INSTALLATION

# create .rvmrc file with the following code:

rvm ree-1.8.7-2012.02@pha --create


# install gems

gem install rails -v=1.2.6
gem install rake -v=0.8.7


# to use gems from vendor/gems add the following code into environment.rb

config.load_paths += Dir["#{RAILS_ROOT}/vendor/gems/**"].map do |dir|
  File.directory?(lib = "#{dir}/lib") ? lib : dir
end


# create database.yml, example:

development:
  adapter: mysql
  encoding: utf8
  database: pha_development
  username: root
  password:
  host: localhost


#create database and load schema

rake _0.8.7_ db:create
rake _0.8.7_ db:schema:load


# loading data

Two options

- download from wiki: https://collab.freeportmetrics.com/attachments/2413/pha.devt.20120415.sql.gz
- clone pha-rubbi: git@freeportmetrics.beanstalkapp.com:/pha-rubbi.git and get data/dump.sql

then load sql file into the database (from command line, via sequel pro or other tool)
